The paper deals with graph theory and optimization problems, specifically the Travelling Salesperson (TSP) and the Steiner Tree problem (STP), which are commonly studied in the computer science subfields of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The introduction of the highway dimension parameter also suggests a potential connection to transportation networks and related fields such as operations research and urban planning.
